The paper deals with the efficient acquisition of an ensemble of correlated signals, which is a problem in signal processing. The use of compressive sampling techniques to acquire the ensemble at a sub-Nyquist rate suggests that the paper belongs to the cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SP (Signal Processing) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of convex programming techniques for matrix recovery, which is a topic in machine learning and optimization, suggesting that it could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.MM (Mathematical Optimization) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses how ensembles of correlated signals arise in the context of array processing, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.SI (Systems and Control) sub-category.
